[2026-03-10T23:03:20Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GsFfdp8LiNf4bSxCYsZbbE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the DSL parsing code. Let me create a detailed summary of my findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration of Cloche Workflow DSL Parsing\n\nI've thoroughly examined the workflow DSL parsing implementation in this Go project. Here's a complete report:\n\n### 1. **Workflow File Parsing Architecture**\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go` - Tokenization\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - AST construction\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go` - Token type definitions\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Domain models and validation\n\n**Parser Structure:**\nThe `Parser` struct (lines 11-16 in parser.go) uses a two-token lookahead pattern:\n- `current` and `peek` tokens\n- Location-aware parsing via `domain.WorkflowLocation` \n- Entry point functions: `Parse()`, `ParseForHost()`, `ParseForContainer()`\n\n### 2. **Lexer Implementation**\n\n**Token Types** (token.go):\n- Structural: `TokenLBrace`, `TokenRBrace`, `TokenLBracket`, `TokenRBracket`, `TokenLParen`, `TokenRParen`\n- Operators: `TokenEquals`, `TokenColon`, `TokenDot`, `TokenArrow`, `TokenComma`\n- Literals: `TokenString`, `TokenInt`, `TokenIdent`\n- Special: `TokenEOF`, `TokenIllegal`\n\n**Lexer Features** (lexer.go, lines 14-94):\n- Handles comments (`//` style, lines 120-127)\n- String escaping for quotes, backslashes, newlines, tabs (lines 130-158)\n- Hyphenated identifiers: `simple-build` is valid (lines 167-169)\n- Arrow operator: `->` (lines 65-75)\n- Line and column tracking for error reporting\n\n### 3. **Step Type Inference**\n\n**Three Step Types** (domain.go, lines 16-20):\n```go\nStepTypeAgent    = \"agent\"    // has 'prompt' field\nStepTypeScript   = \"script\"   // has 'run' field\nStepTypeWorkflow = \"workflow\" // has 'workflow_name' field\n```\n\n**Type Determination** (parser.go, lines 198-227):\n- Inferred from exactly one of: `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`\n- Error if none present or multiple present\n- Location validation enforces: `workflow_name` only allowed in host workflows\n\n### 4. **Agent Step Configuration**\n\n**Agent Command & Args** (at step level, from runner.go):\n\n```go\nagent_command = \"command1,command2,command3\"  // Fallback chain (comma-separated)\nagent_args = \"--flag1 --flag2\"                // Space-separated arguments\n```\n\n**Configuration Levels** (runner.go, lines 53-61):\n\n1. **Environment Variable** (highest priority): `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`\n2. **Workflow-level** (in `container` block): `container.agent_command`, `container.agent_args`\n3. **Step-level** (per-agent step): `agent_command`, `agent_args`\n\nStep-level config overrides workflow-level config (runner.go, lines 133-138).\n\n**Fallback Chain Mechanism** (prompt.go, lines 93-107):\n- Commands are comma-separated and tried in order\n- If a command is not found or fails, the next in chain is attempted\n- Chain stops at first successful command\n- This enables graceful fallback (e.g., claude → custom-agent)\n\n**Parsed Format** (prompt.go, lines 56-65):\n```go\nParseCommands(s string) []string  // splits on comma, trims whitespace\n```\n\nExample from tests: `\"nonexistent-agent-xyz,/path/to/good-agent\"` results in a 2-element fallback chain.\n\n### 5. **Agent Feedback Configuration**\n\n**Feedback Field** (step-level only):\n```go\nfeedback = \"true\"  // Enables per-step feedback injection\n```\n\n**How It Works** (prompt.go, lines 299-305):\n- When `feedback = \"true\"` on an agent step\n- All previous step outputs from `.cloche/output/*.log` are injected into the prompt\n- Formatted as markdown section: `## Validation Output`\n- Used for iterative refinement (fix steps receiving test output)\n\n**Retry Control** (prompt.go, lines 69-79):\n```go\nmax_attempts = \"N\"  // Max retries before returning \"give-up\" result\n```\n\n### 6. **Workflow DSL Syntax**\n\n**Complete Example Structure** (from tests and examples):\n\n```\nworkflow \"name\" {\n  // Workflow-level config (optional)\n  container {\n    image = \"...\"\n    agent_command = \"claude,backup-agent\"\n    agent_args = \"--flags\"\n  }\n\n  // Step definitions\n  step step-name {\n    prompt = file(\"path\") | \"inline string\"    // Agent step\n    run = \"shell command\"                       // Script step  \n    workflow_name = \"other-workflow\"            // Workflow step (host only)\n    \n    // Agent-specific\n    agent_command = \"command1,command2\"         // Fallback chain\n    agent_args = \"--arg1 --arg2\"                // Custom args\n    max_attempts = \"3\"                          // Retry limit\n    feedback = \"true\"                           // Include validation output\n    \n    // Container config per-step\n    container {\n      image = \"custom-image\"\n      network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\"]\n    }\n    \n    results = [success, fail, custom-result]\n  }\n\n  // Wiring: step:result -> next-step [ output mappings ]\n  step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV = output.field, ARR = output[0].id ]\n  step-b:fail -> abort\n  \n  // Parallel branches with collect\n  collect all(step-c:success, step-d:success) -> step-e\n}\n```\n\n### 7. **Output Mapping (Wire Expressions)**\n\n**Wire Output Mapping** (parser.go, lines 414-450):\n\nSyntax: `from:result -> to [ KEY = output.path, KEY = output.path ]`\n\n**Path Expressions**:\n- `output` - Raw output as string\n- `output.field` - JSON object field\n- `output[N]` - Array index (0-based)\n- `output.a.b.c` - Nested field access\n- `output[0].name` - Mixed field and array access\n\n**Implementation** (domain.go, lines 62-69):\n```go\ntype OutputPath struct {\n  Segments []PathSegment\n}\n\ntype PathSegment struct {\n  Kind  SegmentKind  // SegmentField or SegmentIndex\n  Field string       // For field access\n  Index int          // For array indexing\n}\n```\n\n**Evaluation** (domain.go, lines 75-115):\n- JSON parsing for path navigation\n- Returns error if path invalid or type mismatches\n- Converts result to string for env var injection\n\n### 8. **Validation**\n\n**Parse-Time Validation** (domain.go, lines 145-242):\n\n1. **Entry Step Exists** - Workflow must have at least one step\n2. **Result Wiring** - Every result declared must be wired\n3. **Orphan Detection** - All steps must be reachable from entry step\n4. **Location Enforcement** - `workflow_name` only in host workflows\n5. **Duplicate Output Mappings** - Same env var can't be mapped twice to same target step\n\n**Configuration Warnings** (domain.go, lines 259-276):\n- Known keys: `prompt`, `run`, `workflow_name`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `feedback`, `prompt_step`, `results`\n- Warns about unrecognized keys (typo detection)\n\n### 9. **Parser Test Coverage**\n\n**Key Test Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go` - 30+ test cases\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer_test.go` - Tokenization tests\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/mutator_test.go` - DSL mutation (AddStep, AddWiring, UpdateCollect)\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner_test.go` - Integration tests for agent config\n\n**Notable Test Cases:**\n- `TestParser_InfersTypeFromContent` - Type inference validation\n- `TestParser_ContainerBlock` - Per-step container config\n- `TestParser_WorkflowNameStep` - Host workflow dispatch\n- `TestParser_WireArrayIndex`, `TestParser_WireNestedAccess` - Output path expressions\n- `TestRunner_FallbackChain` - Agent command fallback mechanism\n- `TestRunner_StepLevelOverridesWorkflowLevel` - Config precedence\n\n### 10. **Configuration File Examples**\n\n**Workflow-Level Config**:\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` - Host orchestration with output mappings\n- `/workspace/develop.cloche` - Self-evolution workflow with feedback and max_attempts\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/develop.cloche` - Multi-step pipeline with parallel branches (collect all)\n\n**Real-World Patterns**:\n- Parallel branches: `test:success -> lint`, `test:success -> valgrind`, then `collect all(...)`\n- Feedback loops: Fix step receives test output via `feedback = \"true\"`\n- Fallback chains: Used for agent command resilience\n\n### 11. **Known Step Config Keys**\n\nFrom `domain.go` lines 246-257:\n- `prompt`, `run`, `workflow_name` - Step type markers\n- `agent_command`, `agent_args` - Agent configuration\n- `max_attempts`, `timeout` - Execution control\n- `feedback` - Validation output injection\n- `prompt_step` - Reference to another step's prompt (for workflow steps)\n- `results` - Declared result names\n- All `container.*` prefixed keys (per-step container config)\n\n### Summary\n\nThe DSL parsing is a **well-structured two-phase system**:\n\n1. **Lexical Phase** (lexer.go): Converts text to tokens with line/col tracking\n2. **Syntax/Semantic Phase** (parser.go): Builds AST and validates structural rules\n3. **Domain Validation** (domain.go): Enforces workflow graph constraints\n\n**Key Design Patterns**:\n- Type inference from present fields rather than explicit keywords\n- Fallback chains via comma-separated command lists\n- Location-aware validation (host vs container workflows)\n- Output mapping for data flow between steps\n- Configuration hierarchy: env vars > workflow level > step level\n\nAll files are in `/workspace/internal/dsl/` and `/workspace/internal/domain/`, with comprehensive test coverage demonstrating each feature."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a096d4802a4c9b203 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71621\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 52100</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"175df06c-fcc9-44aa-9a28-027165407de1","uuid":"33e9de1b-21bf-4ed5-826c-2edfb8e350f5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the workflow DSL parsing code in this Go project. I need to understand:\n\n1. How workflow files (.c