[2026-03-10T23:03:20Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9TdoBBis1LD81Bra6qw95","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE EXPLORATION REPORT: HOST WORKFLOWS AND AGENT STEP IMPLEMENTATION\n\nI have thoroughly explored the Cloche system. Here's a complete technical overview:\n\n---\n\n### 1. WORKFLOW DSL PARSING & EXECUTION ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Domain types\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - DSL parser\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - DSL specification\n\n**Workflow Types:**\n- **Container Workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`): Run inside Docker container via `cloche-agent`. Support only `agent` and `script` steps.\n- **Host Workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`): Runs on host machine as daemon process. Supports `agent`, `script`, and `workflow` step types.\n\n**Step Type Inference (from `domain/workflow.go` lines 198-229):**\n- `prompt` field → `StepTypeAgent`\n- `run` field → `StepTypeScript`  \n- `workflow_name` field → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host only)\n\n**Known Step Configuration Keys (from `domain/workflow.go` lines 246-257):**\n```go\n\"prompt\", \"run\", \"max_attempts\", \"timeout\", \"agent_command\", \"agent_args\",\n\"results\", \"feedback\", \"workflow_name\", \"prompt_step\"\n```\nPlus prefixed keys like `container.agent_command`, `container.agent_args`, `container.image`, `container.network_allow`\n\n---\n\n### 2. HOST WORKFLOW EXECUTOR (`internal/host/`)\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Host step execution\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Host workflow runner\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop\n\n**Executor (`Executor` struct at line 49-58):**\n- Handles three step types:\n  - **Script**: `executeScript()` - Runs `sh -c` command on host\n  - **Workflow**: `executeWorkflow()` - Dispatches container workflow run\n  - *Note: No agent step support in host workflows*\n\n**Script Execution (`executeScript()` at lines 84-133):**\n- Working directory: `scriptDir()` (MainDir if set, else ProjectDir)\n- Environment variables injected:\n  - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - actual project path\n  - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - path to step output file\n  - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - previous step output (if available)\n  - Output mapping environment variables (from wiring)\n- Result detection: `protocol.ExtractResult()` - looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker\n- Output written to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n\n**Workflow Step Execution (`executeWorkflow()` at lines 136-194):**\n- Reads prompt from `prompt_step` config or previous step's output\n- Dispatches via `RunDispatcher.RunWorkflow()`\n- Links child run to parent host run via `ParentRunID`\n- Writes run ID to step output\n- Polls child run status until terminal state\n- Maps `RunStateSucceeded` → \"success\", others → \"fail\"\n\n**Output Mapping Resolution (`resolveOutputMappings()` at lines 23-42):**\n- Reads source step output files\n- Evaluates path expressions (JSON navigation)\n- Returns KEY=value strings for environment injection\n\n**Host Worktree Support (`MainWorktreeDir()` at lines 248-265):**\n- Uses `git worktree list --porcelain` to find main branch worktree\n- Scripts execute from main branch directory (not linked worktrees)\n- Ensures consistent host-workflow behavior across branches\n\n---\n\n### 3. AGENT STEP IMPLEMENTATION IN CONTAINERS (`cmd/cloche-agent/` & `internal/agent/`)\n\n**Agent Runner (`internal/agent/runner.go`):**\n- Parses container workflow with `dsl.ParseForContainer()`\n- Initializes two adapters: `generic` (script) and `prompt` (agent)\n- Supports workflow-level agent configuration:\n  - `container.agent_command` - comma-separated fallback command chain\n  - `container.agent_args` - custom arguments for all commands\n- Also supports environment variable: `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`\n- Per-step override via `agent_command` and `agent_args` config\n\n**Step Executor (`stepExecutor` at lines 112-148):**\n```go\nswitch step.Type {\ncase StepTypeScript:\n  if step.Config[\"run\"] exists → use generic adapter\ncase StepTypeAgent:\n  if step.Config[\"run\"] exists → use generic adapter (script in agent step)\n  if step.Config[\"prompt\"] exists → use prompt adapter (agent invocation)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. AGENT ADAPTER INTERFACE & IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n**Interface Definition (`internal/ports/agent.go`):**\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Generic Adapter (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`):**\n- Runs shell commands via `exec.CommandContext()`\n- Supports streaming output via `StatusWriter`\n- Extracts result marker from output\n- Logs output to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log`\n\n**Prompt Adapter (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`):**\n\n*Command Fallback Chain (lines 21-52):*\n```go\ndefaultAgentArgs = {\n    \"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"}\n}\n```\n- Commands tried in order; first successful one wins\n- If command not found, tries next in chain\n- Non-fallback conditions: exit 0 OR exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker\n\n*Prompt Assembly (lines 281-319):*\n1. Read system template from `step.Config[\"prompt\"]`\n2. Read user prompt from `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n3. Read feedback from `.cloche/output/*.log` (if `feedback=\"true\"`)\n4. Append result selection instructions\n\n*Attempt Limiting (lines 70-79):*\n- Tracks attempts in `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>`\n- Returns \"give-up\" result if `max_attempts` exceeded\n\n*Streaming Output (lines 158-217):*\n- Parses stream-json format from Claude\n- Extracts text from `content_block_delta` events\n- Streams lines through `StatusWriter` in real-time\n- Accumulates raw output for log file\n\n*Result Classification (lines 222-246):*\n- Exit 0 with output → \"success\" (or marker if present)\n- Exit 0 without output → \"fail\" (auth/config issue)\n- Exit non-zero with marker → returns marker result\n- Exit non-zero without marker → fallback to next command\n\n---\n\n### 5. WORKFLOW EXECUTION ENGINE (`internal/engine/engine.go`)\n\n**StepExecutor Interface (lines 15-18):**\n```go\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Engine Flow:**\n1. Parse & validate workflow\n2. Launch entry step as goroutine\n3. Main event loop processes `stepResult` channel\n4. Validates result is declared in step's `Results` list\n5. Follows wiring to determine next steps\n6. Supports fanout (multiple targets per result)\n7. Handles `collect` conditions for multiple-source convergence\n\n**Timeout Handling (lines 302-311):**\n- Per-step timeout from `step.Config[\"timeout\"]`\n- Defaults to `DefaultStepTimeout = 30 minutes`\n- Enforced via `context.WithTimeout()`\n\n---\n\n### 6. ORCHESTRATION LOOP (`internal/host/loop.go`)\n\n**Loop Management:**\n- Maintains configurable concurrent host workflow runs\n- Staggers launches via `StaggerDelay` (prevents task claiming races)\n- Automatically launches new runs when capacity available\n- Backs off on failure/no-tasks-available (30s poll)\n- Counts only active host runs for concurrency limit\n\n---\n\n### 7. RESULT MARKER PROTOCOL (`internal/protocol/result.go`)\n\n**Marker Format:**\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\n**Extraction (`ExtractResult()`):**\n- Scans output for last occurrence of marker\n- Removes all marker lines from output\n- Returns: (resultName, cleanOutput, found)\n\n**Usage Pattern:**\n- Step execution captures full command output\n- Protocol extracts result marker if present\n- Clean output written to log file\n- If no marker and exit 0 → \"success\"\n- If no marker and exit non-0 → \"fail\"\n\n---\n\n### 8. WORKFLOW FILES ANALYZED\n\n**Host Workflow (`.cloche/host.cloche`):**\n```\n- ready-tasks (script)\n- claim-task (script)\n- prepare-prompt (script)\n- develop (workflow → dispatches container workflow)\n- merge (script)\n- cleanup (script)\n\nWires include output mappings:\n  ready-tasks:success → claim-task [CLOCHE_TASK_ID=output[0].id, ...]\n  prepare-prompt:success → develop [CLOCHE_TASK_ID=output.task_id]\n```\n\n**Container Workflow (`.cloche/develop.cloche`):**\n```\n- implement (agent: prompt)\n- test (script: \"go test ./...\")\n- fix (agent: prompt, max_attempts=\"2\")\n- update-docs (agent: prompt)\n\nNo agent_command/agent_args configuration (uses defaults)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. KEY FEATURES & CAPABILITIES\n\n**Agent Command Configuration:**\n- Workflow-level: `container { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }`\n- Step-level: `agent_command = \"...\"`, `agent_args = \"...\"`\n- Environment variable: `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND=...`\n- Step config overrides workflow config\n\n**Output Path Expressions (in wiring):**\n- `output` - raw string\n- `output.field` - JSON field access\n- `output[N]` - array indexing\n- `output.a.b.c` - deep nesting\n- `output.items[0].name` - mixed paths\n\n**Attempt Limiting:**\n- Per-step `max_attempts = \"N\"` config\n- Tracked in `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>`\n- Returns \"give-up\" result when limit exceeded\n\n**Feedback Mechanism:**\n- Step-level `feedback = \"true\"` config\n- Reads all output logs from `.cloche/output/`\n- Injects into prompt as \"## Validation Output\"\n- Allows agent to fix errors based on test/lint output\n\n**Prompt Components:**\n1. System template (from file or inline)\n2. User request (from `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`)\n3. Validation feedback (optional)\n4. Result selection instructions (auto-generated)\n\n---\n\n### 10. STEP EXECUTION FLOW SUMMARY\n\n**Host Workflow Step:**\n1. Engine launches step via `Executor.Execute()`\n2. For script: runs command, captures output, extracts result marker\n3. For workflow: dispatches container run, polls until completion, maps run state to result\n4. Output written to file for downstream access\n5. Result determines next wiring target\n\n**Container Workflow Agent Step:**\n1. `stepExecutor.Execute()` routes to prompt or generic adapter\n2. If prompt: assembles prompt, invokes agent command with fallback chain\n3. Agent streams output in JSON; text extracted and emitted to StatusWriter\n4. Result marker extracted from output\n5. Output logged to file\n6. Result name returned to engine\n\n---\n\n**All code paths thoroughly analyzed:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3f14d4dc0cf7d7a1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60745\ntool_uses: 35\nduration_ms: 74443</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"175df06c-fcc9-44aa-9a28-027165407de1","uuid":"ed620f43-ecba-4887-bcc9-b92374d338a8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the host workflow executor and agent step implementation in this Go project. I need to understand:\n\n1. How host workflows work (internal/host/ directory)\n2. How agent steps work in container workflows (cloche-agent)\n3. The workflow DSL parsing, especially step types and agent-related configuration\n4. The AgentAdapter interface and implementations\n5. The domain types for workflows and steps\n6. Any existing agent_command, agent_args configuration in the DSL\n\nRead the key files thoroughly. Focus on:\n- internal/host/ (all files)\n- internal/domain/ (workflow, step types)\n- cmd/cloche-agent/ \n- internal/adapters/ (agent-related adapters)\n- internal/ports/ (agent port interface)\n- docs/workflows.md (DSL syntax)\n- .cloche/host.cloche (current host workflow)\n- .cloche/develop.cloche (container workflow for reference)\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely.","agentId":"a3f14d4dc0cf7d7a1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE EXPLORATION REPORT: HOST WORKFLOWS AND AGENT STEP IMPLEMENTATION\n\nI have thoroughly explored the Cloche system. Here's a complete technical overview:\n\n---\n\n### 1. WORKFLOW DSL PARSING & EXECUTION ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Domain types\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - DSL parser\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - DSL specification\n\n**Workflow Types:**\n- **Container Workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`): Run inside Docker container via `cloche-agent`. Support only `agent` and `script` steps.\n- **Host Workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`): Runs on host machine as daemon process. Supports `agent`, `script`, and `workflow` step types.\n\n**Step Type Inference (from `domain/workflow.go` lines 198-229):**\n- `prompt` field → `StepTypeAgent`\n- `run` field → `StepTypeScript`  \n- `workflow_name` field → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host only)\n\n**Known Step Configuration Keys (from `domain/workflow.go` lines 246-257):**\n```go\n\"prompt\", \"run\", \"max_attempts\", \"timeout\", \"agent_command\", \"agent_args\",\n\"results\", \"feedback\", \"workflow_name\", \"prompt_step\"\n```\nPlus prefixed keys like `container.agent_command`, `container.agent_args`, `container.image`, `container.network_allow`\n\n---\n\n### 2. HOST WORKFLOW EXECUTOR (`internal/host/`)\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Host step execution\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Host workflow runner\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop\n\n**Executor (`Executor` struct at line 49-58):**\n- Handles three step types:\n  - **Script**: `executeScript()` - Runs `sh -c` command on host\n  - **Workflow**: `executeWorkflow()` - Dispatches container workflow run\n  - *Note: No agent step support in host workflows*\n\n**Script Execution (`executeScript()` at lines 84-133):**\n- Working directory: `scriptDir()` (MainDir if set, else ProjectDir)\n- Environment variables injected:\n  - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - actual project path\n  - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - path to step output file\n  - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - previous step output (if available)\n  - Output mapping environment variables (from wiring)\n- Result detection: `protocol.ExtractResult()` - looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker\n- Output written to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n\n**Workflow Step Execution (`executeWorkflow()` at lines 136-194):**\n- Reads prompt from `prompt_step` config or previous step's output\n- Dispatches via `RunDispatcher.RunWorkflow()`\n- Links child run to parent host run via `ParentRunID`\n- Writes run ID to step output\n- Polls child run status until terminal state\n- Maps `RunStateSucceeded` → \"success\", others → \"fail\"\n\n**Output Mapping Resolution (`resolveOutputMappings()` at lines 23-42):**\n- Reads source step output files\n- Evaluates path expressions (JSON navigation)\n- Returns KEY=value strings for environment injection\n\n**Host Worktree Support (`MainWorktreeDir()` at lines 248-265):**\n- Uses `git worktree list --porcelain` to find main branch worktree\n- Scripts execute from main branch directory (not linked worktrees)\n- Ensures consistent host-workflow behavior across branches\n\n---\n\n### 3. AGENT STEP IMPLEMENTATION IN CONTAINERS (`cmd/cloche-agent/` & `internal/agent/`)\n\n**Agent Runner (`internal/agent/runner.go`):**\n- Parses container workflow with `dsl.ParseForContainer()`\n- Initializes two adapters: `generic` (script) and `prompt` (agent)\n- Supports workflow-level agent configuration:\n  - `container.agent_command` - comma-separated fallback command chain\n  - `container.agent_args` - custom arguments for all commands\n- Also supports environment variable: `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`\n- Per-step override via `agent_command` and `agent_args` config\n\n**Step Executor (`stepExecutor` at lines 112-148):**\n```go\nswitch step.Type {\ncase StepTypeScript:\n  if step.Config[\"run\"] exists → use generic adapter\ncase StepTypeAgent:\n  if step.Config[\"run\"] exists → use generic adapter (script in agent step)\n  if step.Config[\"prompt\"] exists → use prompt adapter (agent invocation)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. AGENT ADAPTER INTERFACE & IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n**Interface Definition (`internal/ports/agent.go`):**\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Generic Adapter (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`):**\n- Runs shell commands via `exec.CommandContext()`\n- Supports streaming output via `StatusWriter`\n- Extracts result marker from output\n- Logs output to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log`\n\n**Prompt Adapter (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`):**\n\n*Command Fallback Chain (lines 21-52):*\n```go\ndefaultAgentArgs = {\n    \"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"}\n}\n```\n- Commands tried in order; first successful one wins\n- If command not found, tries next in chain\n- Non-fallback conditions: exit 0 OR exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker\n\n*Prompt Assembly (lines 281-319):*\n1. Read system template from `step.Config[\"prompt\"]`\n2. Read user prompt from `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n3. Read feedback from `.cloche/output/*.log` (if `feedback=\"true\"`)\n4. Append result selection instructions\n\n*Attempt Limiting (lines 70-79):*\n- Tracks attempts in `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>`\n- Returns \"give-up\" result if `max_attempts` exceeded\n\n*Streaming Output (lines 158-217):*\n- Parses stream-json format from Claude\n- Extracts text from `content_block_delta` events\n- Streams lines through `StatusWriter` in real-time\n- Accumulates raw output for log file\n\n*Result Classification (lines 222-246):*\n- Exit 0 with output → \"success\" (or marker if present)\n- Exit 0 without output → \"fail\" (auth/config issue)\n- Exit non-zero with marker → returns marker result\n- Exit non-zero without marker → fallback to next command\n\n---\n\n### 5. WORKFLOW EXECUTION ENGINE (`internal/engine/engine.go`)\n\n**StepExecutor Interface (lines 15-18):**\n```go\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Engine Flow:**\n1. Parse & validate workflow\n2. Launch entry step as goroutine\n3. Main event loop processes `stepResult` channel\n4. Validates result is declared in step's `Results` list\n5. Follows wiring to determine next steps\n6. Supports fanout (multiple targets per result)\n7. Handles `collect` conditions for multiple-source convergence\n\n**Timeout Handling (lines 302-311):**\n- Per-step timeout from `step.Config[\"timeout\"]`\n- Defaults to `DefaultStepTimeout = 30 minutes`\n- Enforced via `context.WithTimeout()`\n\n---\n\n### 6. ORCHESTRATION LOOP (`internal/host/loop.go`)\n\n**Loop Management:**\n- Maintains configurable concurrent host workflow runs\n- Staggers launches via `StaggerDelay` (prevents task claiming races)\n- Automatically launches new runs when capacity available\n- Backs off on failure/no-tasks-available (30s poll)\n- Counts only active host runs for concurrency limit\n\n---\n\n### 7. RESULT MARKER PROTOCOL (`internal/protocol/result.go`)\n\n**Marker Format:**\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\n**Extraction (`ExtractResult()`):**\n- Scans output for last occurrence of marker\n- Removes all marker lines from output\n- Returns: (resultName, cleanOutput, found)\n\n**Usage Pattern:**\n- Step execution captures full command output\n- Protocol extracts result marker if present\n- Clean output written to log file\n- If no marker and exit 0 → \"success\"\n- If no marker and exit non-0 → \"fail\"\n\n---\n\n### 8. WORKFLOW FILES ANALYZED\n\n**Host Workflow (`.cloche/host.cloche`):**\n```\n- ready-tasks (script)\n- claim-task (script)\n- prepare-prompt (script)\n- develop (workflow → dispatches container workflow)\n- merge (script)\n- cleanup (script)\n\nWires include output mappings:\n  ready-tasks:success → claim-task [CLOCHE_TASK_ID=output[0].id, ...]\n  prepare-prompt:success → develop [CLOCHE_TASK_ID=output.task_id]\n```\n\n**Container Workflow (`.cloche/develop.cloche`):**\n```\n- implement (agent: prompt)\n- test (script: \"go test ./...\")\n- fix (agent: prompt, max_attempts=\"2\")\n- update-docs (agent: prompt)\n\nNo agent_command/agent_args configuration (uses defaults)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. KEY FEATURES & CAPABILITIES\n\n**Agent Command Configuration:**\n- Workflow-level: `container { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }`\n- Step-level: `agent_command = \"...\"`, `agent_args = \"...\"`\n- Environment variable: `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND=...`\n- Step config overrides workflow config\n\n**Output Path Expressions (in wiring):**\n- `output` - raw string\n- `output.field` - JSON field access\n- `output[N]` - array indexing\n- `output.a.b.c` - deep nesting\n- `output.items[0].name` - mixed paths\n\n**Attempt Limiting:**\n- Per-step `max_attempts = \"N\"` config\n- Tracked in `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>`\n- Returns \"give-up\" result when limit exceeded\n\n**Feedback Mechanism:**\n- Step-level `feedback = \"true\"` config\n- Reads all output logs from `.cloche/output/`\n- Injects into prompt as \"## Validation Output\"\n- Allows agent to fix errors based on test/lint output\n\n**Prompt Components:**\n1. System template (from file or inline)\n2. User request (from `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`)\n3. Validation feedback (optional)\n4. Result selection instructions (auto-generated)\n\n---\n\n### 10. STEP EXECUTION FLOW SUMMARY\n\n**Host Workflow Step:**\n1. Engine launches step via `Executor.Execute()`\n2. For script: runs command, captures output, extracts result marker\n3. For workflow: dispatches container run, polls until completion, maps run state to result\n4. Output written to file for downstream access\n5. Result determines next wiring target\n\n**Container Workflow Agent Step:**\n1. `stepExecutor.Execute()` routes to prompt or generic adapter\n2. If prompt: assembles prompt, invokes agent command with fallback chain\n3. Agent streams output in JSON; text extracted and emitted to StatusWriter\n4. Result marker extracted from output\n5. Output logged to file\n6. Result name returned to engine\n\n---\n\n**All code paths thoroughly analyzed:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":74443,"totalTokens":60745,"totalToolUseCount":35,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":162,"cache_read_input_tokens":57445,"output_tokens":3138,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":162},"inference_g