[2026-03-10T23:05:02Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Awb3R57dzu7TQwyZfArQZn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche Usage\n     2→\n     3→Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4→workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5→container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6→results to a git branch.\n     7→\n     8→## Core Concepts\n     9→\n    10→- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11→- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12→- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13→- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14→- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15→\n    16→## Workflow DSL\n    17→\n    18→Workflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19→declared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20→no orphans, entry point exists).\n    21→\n    22→### Minimal Example\n    23→\n    24→```\n    25→workflow \"develop\" {\n    26→  step implement {\n    27→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28→    results = [success, fail]\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  step test {\n    32→    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33→    results = [success, fail]\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  implement:success -> test\n    37→  implement:fail -> abort\n    38→  test:success -> done\n    39→  test:fail -> abort\n    40→}\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→### Step Configuration\n    44→\n    45→| Key | Type | Description |\n    46→|-----|------|-------------|\n    47→| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48→| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49→| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50→| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51→| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52→| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53→| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54→| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55→| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56→| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57→\n    58→A step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59→\n    60→### The `file()` Function\n    61→\n    62→`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63→(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64→templates:\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68→```\n    69→\n    70→### The `container {}` Block\n    71→\n    72→Can appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73→\n    74→**Step level** — per-step container config:\n    75→```\n    76→step code {\n    77→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78→  container {\n    79→    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81→    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82→  }\n    83→  results = [success, fail]\n    84→}\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n    88→```\n    89→workflow \"develop\" {\n    90→  container {\n    91→    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92→    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94→  }\n    95→  ...\n    96→}\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→Supported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100→\n   101→### Wiring Syntax\n   102→\n   103→Connect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   104→\n   105→```\n   106→implement:success -> test\n   107→implement:fail -> abort\n   108→test:success -> done\n   109→test:fail -> fix\n   110→```\n   111→\n   112→### Wire Output Mappings\n   113→\n   114→Extract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   115→\n   116→```\n   117→step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   118→```\n   119→\n   120→Path expressions:\n   121→\n   122→| Expression | Meaning |\n   123→|---|---|\n   124→| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   125→| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   126→| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   127→| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   128→| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   129→\n   130→If the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   131→text, only bare `output` works.\n   132→\n   133→### Retry Loops\n   134→\n   135→Wire failures back to earlier steps:\n   136→\n   137→```\n   138→test:fail -> fix\n   139→fix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   140→fix:fail -> abort\n   141→```\n   142→\n   143→Use `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   144→\n   145→```\n   146→step fix {\n   147→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   148→  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   149→  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   150→}\n   151→```\n   152→\n   153→### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   154→\n   155→Wire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   156→\n   157→```\n   158→test:success -> lint\n   159→test:success -> quality\n   160→```\n   161→\n   162→### Collect (Join)\n   163→\n   164→Synchronize parallel branches:\n   165→\n   166→```\n   167→collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   168→collect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   169→```\n   170→\n   171→`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   172→\n   173→### Comments\n   174→\n   175→Line comments with `//`:\n   176→\n   177→```\n   178→// This is a comment\n   179→implement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   180→```\n   181→\n   182→## Result Protocol\n   183→\n   184→Steps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   185→\n   186→```\n   187→CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   188→```\n   189→\n   190→For example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   191→\n   192→Rules:\n   193→- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   194→- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   195→- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   196→- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   197→- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   198→\n   199→## Prompt Assembly\n   200→\n   201→When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   202→\n   203→1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   204→2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   205→3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   206→4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   207→\n   208→The assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   209→\n   210→## Agent Command Resolution\n   211→\n   212→Priority (highest to lowest):\n   213→1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   214→2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n   215→3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   216→4. Default: `claude`\n   217→\n   218→### Fallback Chains\n   219→\n   220→Comma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   221→\n   222→```\n   223→agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→- **Command not found / failed to start** — try next command\n   227→- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n   228→- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n   229→- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n   230→- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n   231→- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n   232→\n   233→Known agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   234→\n   235→## Workflow Locations\n   236→\n   237→**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   238→via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   239→\n   240→**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   241→Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   242→dispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   243→execute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   244→fixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   245→\n   246→### Host Workflow Example\n   247→\n   248→```\n   249→workflow \"main\" {\n   250→  step ready-tasks {\n   251→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n   252→    results = [success, fail]\n   253→  }\n   254→\n   255→  step prepare-prompt {\n   256→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   257→    results = [success, fail]\n   258→  }\n   259→\n   260→  step develop {\n   261→    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   262→    results       = [success, fail]\n   263→  }\n   264→\n   265→  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n   266→    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n   267→    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n   268→    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n   269→  ]\n   270→  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n   271→  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n   272→  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   273→  develop:success        -> done\n   274→  develop:fail           -> done\n   275→}\n   276→```\n   277→\n   278→### Host Step Environment Variables\n   279→\n   280→| Variable | Description |\n   281→|----------|-------------|\n   282→| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   283→| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   284→| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   285→| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n   286→\n   287→### Container Environment Variables\n   288→\n   289→| Variable | Description |\n   290→|----------|-------------|\n   291→| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   292→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   293→| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   294→\n   295→## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   296→\n   297→```\n   298→workflow \"develop\" {\n   299→  step implement {\n   300→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   301→    results = [success, fail]\n   302→  }\n   303→\n   304→  step test {\n   305→    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   306→    results = [success, fail]\n   307→  }\n   308→\n   309→  step lint {\n   310→    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   311→    results = [success, fail]\n   312→  }\n   313→\n   314→  step quality {\n   315→    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   316→    results = [success, fail]\n   317→  }\n   318→\n   319→  step fix {\n   320→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   321→    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   322→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   323→  }\n   324→\n   325→  implement:success -> test\n   326→  implement:fail -> abort\n   327→\n   328→  test:success -> lint\n   329→  test:success -> quality\n   330→  test:fail -> fix\n   331→\n   332→  lint:fail -> fix\n   333→  quality:fail -> fix\n   334→  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   335→\n   336→  fix:success -> test\n   337→  fix:fail -> abort\n   338→  fix:give-up -> abort\n   339→}\n   340→```\n   341→\n   342→## Container Isolation Model\n   343→\n   344→- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   345→- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   346→- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   347→- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   348→- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   349→\n   350→Your project directory is never modified by the container.\n   351→\n   352→## CLI Reference\n   353→\n   354→### `cloche init`\n   355→\n   356→Scaffold a new Cloche project.\n   357→\n   358→```\n   359→cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   360→```\n   361→\n   362→| Flag | Default | Description |\n   363→|------|---------|-------------|\n   364→| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   365→| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   366→\n   367→Creates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   368→host workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   369→\n   370→### `cloche run`\n   371→\n   372→Launch a workflow run.\n   373→\n   374→```\n   375→cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   376→```\n   377→\n   378→| Flag | Description |\n   379→|------|-------------|\n   380→| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   381→| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   382→| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   383→| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   384→\n   385→Must be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   386→when `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   387→\n   388→### `cloche status`\n   389→\n   390→```\n   391→cloche status <run-id>\n   392→```\n   393→\n   394→Shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   395→\n   396→### `cloche list`\n   397→\n   398→```\n   399→cloche list [--all]\n   400→```\n   401→\n   402→Lists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n   403→\n   404→### `cloche logs`\n   405→\n   406→```\n   407→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n   408→```\n   409→\n   410→| Flag | Description |\n   411→|------|-------------|\n   412→| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   413→| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   414→| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n   415→\n   416→For active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n   417→\n   418→### `cloche poll`\n   419→\n   420→```\n   421→cloche poll <run-id>\n   422→```\n   423→\n   424→Block until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   425→\n   426→### `cloche stop`\n   427→\n   428→```\n   429→cloche stop <run-id>\n   430→```\n   431→\n   432→### `cloche delete`\n   433→\n   434→```\n   435→cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   436→```\n   437→\n   438→Delete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   439→\n   440→### `cloche health`\n   441→\n   442→```\n   443→cloche health\n   444→```\n   445→\n   446→Show per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   447→\n   448→### `cloche shutdown`\n   449→\n   450→```\n   451→cloche shutdown\n   452→```\n   453→\n   454→## Project Layout\n   455→\n   456→```\n   457→my-project/\n   458→├── .cloche/\n   459→│   ├── develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   460→│   ├── host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   461→│   ├── Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   462→│   ├── config.toml           # Project configuration\n   463→│   ├── prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   464→│   │   ├── implement.md\n   465→│   │   ├── fix.md\n   466→│   │   └── update-docs.md\n   467→│   ├── scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   468→│   ├── overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   469→│   │   └── CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   470→│   └── <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   471→│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   472→│       ├── output/\n   473→│       │   ├── full.log      # Unified log\n   474→│       │   ├── test.log      # Per-step script output\n   475→│       │   └── llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   476→│       ├── attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   477→│       └── history.log       # Step execution log\n   478→├── src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   479→└── .git/\n   480→```\n   481→\n   482→## Daemon Configuration\n   483→\n   484→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   485→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   486→| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   487→| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   488→| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   489→| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   490→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   491→| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   492→| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   493→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   494→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   495→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   496→\n   497→### Client Configuration\n   498→\n   499→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   500→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   501→| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   502→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   503→\n   504→## Dockerfile Requirements\n   505→\n   506→The container image must have:\n   507→- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   508→- `git` installed\n   509→- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   510→- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   511→- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   512→\n   513→## Build Commands\n   514→\n   515→```\n   516→make build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   517→make test           # Run all tests\n   518→make test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   519→make lint           # Run go vet\n   520→make proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   521→make docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   522→make install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   523→make clean          # Remove bin/\n   524→```\n   525→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55172401-7cfb-45c6-9eaa-fc2da58fa839","uuid":"f1e76922-62b0-467b-91f9-4caa225abb82","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"# Cloche Usage\n\nCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\nworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\ncontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\nresults to a git branch.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\ndeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\nno orphans, entry point exists).\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### Step Configuration\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n\nA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n\n### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** — per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)\n\nSynchronize parallel branches:\n\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\ncollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n\n### Comments\n\nLine comments with `//`:\n\n```\n// This is a comment\nimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n```\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n\nRules:\n- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n### Fallback Chains\n\nComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n\n```\nagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n```\n\n- **Command not found / failed to start** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n\n## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\nexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\nfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n\n### Host Workflow Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n  ]\n  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n```\n\n### Host Step Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n\n### Container Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n\n## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step lint {\n    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step quality {\n    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n\n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Container Isolation Model\n\n- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n\nYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n\n## CLI Reference\n\n### `cloche init`\n\nScaffold a new Cloche project.\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n\nCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\nhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n\n### `cloche run`\n\nLaunch a workflow run.\n\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n\nFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche shutdown`\n\n```\ncloche shutdown\n```\n\n## Project Layout\n\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n│   ├── host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n│   ├── Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n│   ├── config.toml           # Project configuration\n│   ├── prompts/              # Prompt templates\n│   │   ├── implement.md\n│   │   ├── fix.md\n│   │   └── update-docs.md\n│   ├── scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n│   ├── overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n│   │   └── CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n│   └── <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt\n│       ├── output/\n│       │   ├── full.log      # Unified log\n│       │   ├── test.log      # Per-step script output\n│       │   └── llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n│       ├── attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n│       └── history.log       # Step execution log\n├── src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n└── .git/\n```\n\n## Daemon Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":525,"startLine":1,"totalLines":525}}}
